      About this item

      • 4K Ultra HD Night Vision - Record real-time live video with 4K Ultra HD (8MP, 3840 x 2160) cameras. The 18pcs powerful infrared LEDs emit lights that pierce the darkness up to 100 feet. Advanced 3D-DNR technology dramatically reduces noise levels. Say no to blurry images and embrace the 4k definition.
      • Person/Vehicle Detection - Smart PoE IP cameras can identify people and vehicles in terms of their shapes, minimizing unwanted alerts such as animals or shadows. Cameras can also be configured to specify the type of detection when sending alerts to you. Know what happened simply by glancing at the lock screen.
      • Plug and Play PoE System - Connect the security cameras to the NVR with Ethernet cables up to 300ft, download the free Repolink APP and add the device information on APP. Just 3 steps for 24/7 surveillance purposes. Then you can live view and review locally through a monitor (not included) or remotely via Reolink app anytime, anywhere. Unlike wireless cameras, POE can offer a lossless video signal and a more stable network connection.
      • Continuous 24/7 Recording - With a pre-installed 2TB HDD, you are provided with reliable 24/7 recording. You can also install an external hard drive (up to 6TB) for backup storage.
      • 2-Year Warranty & Life-Time Tech Support - Reolink products have a 2-year warranty and lifetime tech support. Fell free to contact Reolink anytime for any questions or problems via Amazon message or email.

      Product Description

      RLK8-800B6

      Make Security Easier with No Compromise

      Reolink Smart 4K Ultra-HD Security Camera System with Person & Vehicle Detection

      Great Details in 4K Ultra HD, Peaceful 24/7

      4K Ultra-HD video clarity helps keep all the details sharp day and night. Reliable NVR local storage and Reolink software allows checking anytime anywhere you want.

      Smart Motion Detection

      Smart Detection, Identify True Threats

      Smart detection of people and vehicles filters out unwanted alerts such as those triggered by bugs and leaves. Save your time and energy over general motion detection. You can also set and apply general motion detection or 24/7 recording as needed.

      Instant Push, Take Actions Timely

      A prompt email & push notification will be sent to users smart devices once moving objects are detected, allowing for quick action. Buzzer in the NVR will alert you and FTP uploading will be underway for backup. Share access with your colleagues or family for surveillance together with no charge.

      Amazon Customer
      5 out of 5 stars
      Impressed by build quality and performance
      I previously owned a different (cheaper, different brand) wifi-based system, that did well, but had the downfalls of requiring internet to work, and also couldnt record continuous (it would be like 5 or 10 second gaps between recordings, and also if multiple cameras engaged recording motions at once, sometimes it would miss some events). This system is a full standalone system that only requires internet for the app should you chose to use it. This 4K system is a significant image improvement, and has a pretty good night vision range too. Being 4K, it allows you to make out smaller details easier, such as license plates, or see a little further than lower resolution images. Audio quality I rate as moderate. I bought the 6 camera system, but just using 5 cameras for now, at 4K and including audio, it gets to roughly 6.5 days of recording on the 2TB drive so far before writing over old videos with my experience. I also really like the wired system vs wifi systems now, the image quality, and frame rate is much better, and also eliminates any network interference issues or artifacts from data transmission (which I ran into sometimes with my previous WiFi systems). Also being a POE system, no other wires for power needed, nor have to worry about any batteries to change or recharge. Running the wiring (to hide it professionally) is a big task, I ran mine behind the siding in places and then down through my subfloor/basement, this can be a drawback vs wifi, as it does require a mechanically inclined person, or recommend hiring someone to do so. I originally was curious if enough wiring was included to run all the wires, and indeed it was (just barely on one camera). Initial setup is a little quirky with the mouse included with the control unit, almost would need a keyboard, because typing is more difficult using a mouse to access a digital keyboard on screen, but once setup, I do everything else with the app now. The app does take getting used to, to learn the different functions and what they do, it is more robust than the previous type I had. I can do everything remotely with the app that I have noticed, including fully rebooting or updating the control unit (I think I remember having to enable something to allow for remote access on the control screen, or leave it off if you chose to only use the control unit locally). I have grown to really like it once I learned it. Very impressed indeed, and well worth the price (I caught it on a lightning sale). Would recommend this brand , and specifically this model to anyone interested.

I have grown to really like it once I learned it. Very impressed indeed, and well worth the price (I caught it on a lightning sale). Would recommend this brand , and specifically this model to anyone interested.

      • Martha3065
        4.0 out of 5 stars Overall pretty good. Room for improvement.
        Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2020
        Verified Purchase
        This is a really good system. This is my first surveillance system and I am not a professional, so take that into account.

        I read reviews and some comparisons before pulling the trigger. Ended up getting this knowing some of the shortcomings.

        Easy to install if you have DIY capabilities. Had to drill some holes and fish some wires. Install is clean and looks professional. Just connect the wires to the NVR and go. NVR software was pretty easy to setup.

        Clarity during the daylight is amazing. I am recording in 4K but displayed on a 1080P HD Samsung TV. Amazing! Would look better on a 4K TV. The attached pics are from the app which is at a reduced quality. You can stream to the app at full 4K if desired.

        Some limitations:
        1. Zoom is digital (pixel enlargement), so image will lose quality as you zoom.
        2. Movement detection is digital/pixel based so will pick up anything that moves within the pixels. Moving shadows, branches, spider webs. Because of this I have alarms shut off. Software allows you to jump to movement triggers. Some other camera/NVR options have thermal imaging to help with this.
        3. Night vision is good but focuses light toward the center which limits the distance if the camera is angled downward. This can be seen in some of the attached night images. Peripheral distance is limited.
        4. License plates reflect light, including infrared. You won't be able to read them at night through the cameras.

        NVR software is intuitive. Mouse isn't the greatest but works. Keyboard integration would be nice. Phone app is pretty good. So many options it takes a while to navigate them all. Both the software and app allow masking private areas to not record and areas to track motion.

        Overall pretty happy with the purchase and quality. Would buy again and recommend to others.
